abstract: From the opening bell, Democrats savaged New York billionaire Mike Bloomberg and raised pointed questions about Bernie Sanders' take-no-prisoners politics during a contentious debate Wednesday night that threatened to further muddy the party's urgent quest to defeat President Donald Trump.
snippet: From the opening bell, Democrats savaged New York billionaire Mike Bloomberg and raised pointed questions about Bernie Sanders' take-no-prisoners politics during a contentious debate Wednesday night that threatened to further muddy the party's urg...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — From the opening bell, Democrats savaged New York billionaire Mike Bloomberg and raised pointed questions about Bernie Sanders' take-no-prisoners politics during a contentious debate Wednesday night that threatened to further muddy the party's urgent quest to defeat President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Debate Night Brawl: Bloomberg, Sanders Attacked by Rivals
headline_print_headline: Debate Night Brawl: Bloomberg, Sanders Attacked by Rivals

abstract: The virus continues to spread in China, though more slowly. New cases in countries like Japan and Iran have experts concerned about getting it under control quickly.
snippet: The virus continues to spread in China, though more slowly. New cases in countries like Japan and Iran have experts concerned about getting it under control quickly.
lead_paragraph: Two passengers from the cruise ship quarantined in Japan have died after contracting the new coronavirus, the first deaths among the more than 600 people on board who have been infected,  a Japanese health ministry official said on Thursday.

abstract: A state lawmaker and a school board president won primaries Tuesday to earn the right to run for an open seat in northern Wisconsin's 7th Congressional District once held by a reality TV star.
snippet: A state lawmaker and a school board president won primaries Tuesday to earn the right to run for an open seat in northern Wisconsin's 7th Congressional District once held by a reality TV star.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — A state lawmaker and a school board president won primaries Tuesday to earn the right to run for an open seat in northern Wisconsin's 7th Congressional District once held by a reality TV star.
headline_main: Senator, School Leader Win Wisconsin Congressional Primary
headline_print_headline: Senator, School Leader Win Wisconsin Congressional Primary

abstract: Japan recorded a trade deficit for the month of January Wednesday, as exports declined amid worries about the spread of a new virus that could deaden regional economic growth.
snippet: Japan recorded a trade deficit for the month of January Wednesday, as exports declined amid worries about the spread of a new virus that could deaden regional economic growth.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japan recorded a trade deficit for the month of January Wednesday, as exports declined amid worries about the spread of a new virus that could deaden regional economic growth.
headline_main: Japan Records Trade Deficit in January Amid Growth Fears
headline_print_headline: Japan Records Trade Deficit in January Amid Growth Fears

abstract: Attorney General William Barr has told people close to him he’s considering quitting his post after President Donald Trump wouldn’t heed his warning to stop tweeting about Justice Department cases, an administration official told The Associated Press.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General William Barr has told people close to him he’s considering quitting his post after President Donald Trump wouldn’t heed his warning to stop tweeting about Justice Department cases, an administration official told The Associated Press.
headline_main: AP Source: Barr Tells People He Might Quit Over Trump Tweets
headline_print_headline: AP Source: Barr Tells People He Might Quit Over Trump Tweets

abstract: President Donald Trump began a four-day Western swing on Tuesday with a fundraiser in Los Angeles, the first stop on a trip aimed at making himself a distraction as Democratic presidential candidates focus on the Nevada caucuses.
snippet: President Donald Trump began a four-day Western swing on Tuesday with a fundraiser in Los Angeles, the first stop on a trip aimed at making himself a distraction as Democratic presidential candidates focus on the Nevada caucuses.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — President Donald Trump began a four-day Western swing on Tuesday with a fundraiser in Los Angeles, the first stop on a trip aimed at making himself a distraction as Democratic presidential candidates focus on the Nevada caucuses.
headline_main: Trump Aims to Be Distraction for Democrats on Western U.S. Swing
headline_print_headline: Trump Aims to Be Distraction for Democrats on Western U.S. Swing

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he is considering a visit to Japan this summer for the Olympic Games in Tokyo, a trip that would take him off the campaign trail as he seeks re-election.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he is considering a visit to Japan this summer for the Olympic Games in Tokyo, a trip that would take him off the campaign trail as he seeks re-election.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he is considering a visit to Japan this summer for the Olympic Games in Tokyo, a trip that would take him off the campaign trail as he seeks re-election.
headline_main: Trump Considering Travel to Tokyo for Summer Olympics
headline_print_headline: Trump Considering Travel to Tokyo for Summer Olympics

abstract: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg will sell Bloomberg LP, the financial information company that made him a billionaire, if he is elected to the White House in November, his campaign confirmed on Tuesday.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg will sell Bloomberg LP, the financial information company that made him a billionaire, if he is elected to the White House in November, his campaign confirmed on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic presidential contender Michael Bloomberg will sell Bloomberg LP, the financial information company that made him a billionaire, if he is elected to the White House in November, his campaign confirmed on Tuesday.
headline_main: Bloomberg to Sell His Company if Elected President: Campaign
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg to Sell His Company if Elected President: Campaign

abstract: After spending over $400 million promoting himself, Michael Bloomberg faces the scrutiny of a debate for the first time.
snippet: After spending over $400 million promoting himself, Michael Bloomberg faces the scrutiny of a debate for the first time.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, the leading Democratic candidates for president will take the debate stage in Las Vegas, three days ahead of the Nevada caucuses. This will be the race’s ninth debate, and many voters may be tempted to skip the show. That would be a mistake.
